Thank you for your interest in Dean College. Our admissions staff is here to help you throughout the process.
Ready to apply? Show us who you are! There are two ways to apply; the Common Application or the Dean College Application.
At Dean College we make the application process simple. For details on the application process see below.
November 1: Early Action Priority Deadline (Receive Decision Mid-December)
December 1: Early Action Deadline (Receive Decision Mid-January)

Dean College admits students of any race, color, national and ethnic origin to all the rights, privileges, programs and activities generally accorded or made available to students at the College.  Dean College does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, age, gender, sexual orientation, religion, disability, marital status, veteran status, nation and ethnic origin in administration of its educational policies, admissions policies, scholarship and loan programs and athletic and other College-administered programs.

If you are ready to discover The Dean Difference, then don't wait to apply.
Dean College offers an Early Action Plan that will allow you to receive an earlier decision on your application.
Those applying by November 1st should submit all required application materials (transcripts, recommendations, etc.) by November 20th for a decision by December 15th.
Those applying by December 1st should submit all required application materials (transcripts, recommendations, etc.) by December 20th for a decision by January 15th.
Pay your enrollment deposit by May 1st to hold your place in the class
We can review your application without your first semester senior grades.
You'll receive your scholarship award sooner (awards average $15,000/year!).
You'll receive top priority for housing registration.
You won't have to wait to get an admissions decision!
Information for Dance or Theatre Applicants

In addition to the regular application for admission requirements, applicants to degree programs in Dance or Theatre are required to complete an on-campus audition. To be considered as an Early Action applicant, applicants to these programs should schedule their audition for an available date before Nov. 20th / Dec. 20th. Find information on
available audition dates and the process

In addition to the regular application for admission requirements, applicants to the Arch Program have additional requirements, including an interview for the program. To be considered as an Early Action applicant, applicants to the Arch Program should schedule their interview for an available date before Nov. 20th / Dec. 20th.

Parents and family members play an important role in helping students make the most of their experience at Dean College. We encourage you to stay connected and get involved in the Dean Community.

At Dean, families are informed about their student every step of the way. You are part of our community too. Monthly newsletters are sent to families via email by the Assistant Vice President of Student Life and Dean of Students, Dave Drucker.

The Difference is really quite simple —
To the strong and faithful nothing is difficult.

The Center for Business, Entertainment & Sport Management

The Center has forged strategic partnerships with giants in the sports and entertainment industries, like the New England Patriots, New England Revolution, WEEI Sports Radio, Patriot Place, Providence Sports Entertainment and the Pawtucket Red Sox to give students one-of-a-kind opportunities in a variety of competitive fields.
From our small class sizes and personalized attention to our strong emphasis on individualized learning, we meet you where you are to help you achieve your academic goals and career dreams.
